2:T901,[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Place","name":"Flatiron","description":"The Flatiron District takes its name from the iconic triangular building at 23rd Street and Fifth Avenue — one of New York's most photographed structures, visible from nearly every block in the neighb","url":"https://withpush.co/neighborhoods/flatiron","geo":{"@type":"GeoCoordinates","latitude":40.7412,"longitude":-73.9899},"address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"Flatiron","addressRegion":"NY","addressCountry":"US"},"containedInPlace":{"@type":"City","name":"New York City"}},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does Push work in Flatiron?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Push connects local creators with merchants in Flatiron, Manhattan. Creators visit participating businesses, scan a QR code to verify their visit, then publish content. Merchants pay only for verified foot traffic — no guessing required."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many campaigns are active in Flatiron right now?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Flatiron currently has 22 active creator campaigns across 29 merchants, with 98 creators operating in this neighborhood."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the average campaign payout in Flatiron?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The average campaign payout in Flatiron is $43 per verified visit. Total verified visits in this neighborhood have reached 2,743."}}]},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"ItemList","name":"Featured Merchants in Flatiron","numberOfItems":3,"itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Shake Shack Madison Square Park","address":"Madison Square Park, New York, NY 10010","description":"Food & Drink business in Flatiron with 2 active Push campaigns."}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Eataly NYC Flatiron","address":"200 5th Ave, New York, NY 10010","description":"Food & Drink business in Flatiron with 3 active Push campaigns."}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"La Pecora Bianca","address":"1133 Broadway, New York, NY 10010","description":"Food & Drink business in Flatiron with 1 active Push campaign."}}]}]4:T428,The Flatiron District takes its name from the iconic triangular building at 23rd Street and Fifth Avenue — one of New York's most photographed structures, visible from nearly every block in the neighborhood. The surrounding streets have become a hub for tech companies, media agencies, and the restaurants and coffee bars that serve them. Madison Square Park is the neighborhood's living room: farmers markets, public art installations, and Shake Shack's original location anchor a civic square that draws both tourists and workers. Push campaigns in Flatiron skew corporate-adjacent — merchants know their customer is often a professional lunch crowd with a 45-minute window. Quick-service, counter-service, and delivery-first restaurants dominate, but the neighborhood also supports a strong coffee shop creator economy. The NoMad sub-district to the north adds luxury hotel bars and destination restaurants to the mix. Creator campaigns run consistently Monday through Friday in Flatiron, with a pronounced midday surge unlike most other Push neighborhoods.0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$2"}}],["$","main",null,{"className":"nh-page","children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"nhd-hero","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container nhd-hero-inner","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"nhd-breadcrumb","aria-label":"Breadcrumb","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/","children":"Push"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"nhd-breadcrumb-sep","children":"/"}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/neighborhoods","children":"Neighborhoods"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"nhd-breadcrumb-sep"